Tests added for many classes. 30% increased branch coverage and quality corrections. Currently the maven plugin has reached 70% in total of branch coverage. Animation tests for Automato, Book, Library, Borrower, are extensive and test all the available inputs of the stream x machines. 14 integration tests are now available for all the implemented examples. The integration tests include compilation, generation, banimation, animation and transformation. Groovy validation for integration tests have been created for each different example to ensure successful builds. The groovy validation checks every file(xml tests, junits tests, java SXMs, compiled classes, definitions implementations, definitions classes, copied adapters, inputs.xml and output.xml) generated by the tool and deletes them upon completion in order to prepare the build for next run and decrease file size. Use -Dshit -Dcolor=false -Dverbose=true to run the integration tests. MOJOS have been tested heavily and currently cover 85% of the code branches. Removed bug when creating tests for external implementations. Many imports were causing corrupted test package.

Animation tests for Automato, Book, Library, Borrower, are extensive and test all the available inputs of the stream x machines. 14 integration tests are now available for all the implemented examples. The integration tests include compilation, generation, banimation, animation and transformation. Groovy validation for integration tests have been created for each different example to ensure successful builds. The groovy validation checks every file(xml tests, junits tests, java SXMs, compiled classes, definitions implementations, definitions classes, copied adapters, inputs.xml and output.xml) generated by the tool and deletes them upon completion in order to prepare the build for next run and decrease file size. Use -Dshit -Dcolor=false -Dverbose=true to run the integration tests. MOJOS have been tested heavily and currently cover 85% of the code branches. Removed bug when creating tests for external implementations. Many imports were causing corrupted test package.

New logging options at pom.xml. The 3 different appenders console, html, and txt, can now be customized. Logging level can be set for each appender. For example the console logging Level can be set to OFF(no information at all), the html to WARN(printing only WARN and ERROR messages) and the txt appender to DEBUG. By default all appenders are set to INFO. This approach provides full logging capabilities without being needed to recompile jsxm-maven-plugin with new logging levels. Another great advantage is the fact that each specification can be DEBUG instantly without the need for special debugging version. More info about this upgrade will be documented in the manual.

Issued version 1.2. Multi threaded operation are available for all the main goals of the plugin(validation-compilation-generation-creation). Cleared duplicate code for non multi threaded operation. Single threaded execution uses again thread but from a single threaded pool.
Corrected unexpected behaviour of threads when accessing simultaneously code from same class.Added new maven goals.Functionality to extract all the java package structure and create similar structure for the jsxm specifications. Functionality to add all the specifications as classpath entries for easy navigation in the eclipse IDE . Added individual logging capability for each specification. Each specification logs info to a unique log file and is characterized by the specification name. Added general-log file that logs general info regarding the plugin execution.
Refactored Animation phase of plugin. Created Abstract class for Animation that will be used by all different animation implementations.Corrected class names following standard naming conventions. Corrected package structure and restructured it following the different phases of the plugin. Additional info regarding this commit will be documented and commited as soon as possible.

New goal validate-jsxm introduced. Along with the goal a new facade validate and a new step validate were created in the jsxm tool. Validate goal will run before every compilation of the jsxm. Additionally the goals are dependent with each other and invoke the necessary goals in order to avoid errors during phases. The compile-jsxm goal is dependent on validate-jsxm and validate will run before compilation phase is entered. The goal generate-jsxm is dependent on compile-jsxm goal and will cause a transtitive dependency to be called, because compile-jsxm will then call validate. Finally, the goals animate and banimate depend on compile-jsxm goal. If the validate goal fails for any reason jsxm will step over all the phases and will exit. The validate goal must succeed 100% in order for the tool to continue with the next phases. Some methods were moved from the maven goals to Function class in order to avoid repetition. Animation is providing a new feature, this of saving the animation in a input_xml file. The animation can be saved an any point and will produce an [specName]_input.xml in the animation folder of the animated model (all the calls and inputs that were used during the animation process). Saving the model follows the same process and makes the same checks that animation is using, so to ensure that a valid xml file will be generated. The exported xml file can be later used for batch animation. The extension of the input changed to xml (previously it was .jsxm) for compatibility with the xml editors.

JSXM -maven-plugin serves as an interface for the JSXM tool. It provides 13 different goals each bound to a different phase. The available goals of the jsxm-maven-plugin are, validate, compile, compile-repast, generate, animate-console, animate-gui banimate, create-sample, copy-external-package, copy-package, classpath, profile and help.
